methods.closeTimeout:
The Session and ConsoleSession close timeout. By default, is PT5s. The default can be
 overridden via the system property deephaven.session.closeTimeout.

:return: (java.time.Duration) the close timeout
methods.delegateToBatch:
Whether the Session implementation will implement a batch TableHandleManager. By default, is
 false. The default can be overridden via the system property deephaven.session.batch.

:return: (boolean) true if the session will implement a batch manager, false if the session will implement a serial manager
methods.executeTimeout:
The session execute timeout. By default, is PT1m. The default can be overridden via the system property
 deephaven.session.executeTimeout.

:return: (java.time.Duration) the session execute timeout
methods.mixinStacktrace:
Whether the default batch TableHandleManager will use mix-in more relevant stacktraces. By default, is
 false. The default can be overridden via the system property deephaven.session.batch.stacktraces.

:return: (boolean) true if the default batch manager will mix-in stacktraces, false otherwise
